    <item>
      <title>Progression Idea</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=15554#M15554</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Personally, I am fine with the idea of the server as it is. But when I read the forums it is easy to see&amp;nbsp;that people want different things from this server. One thing I see that may be a potential problem with the combine is there is going to be extreme competition for some of the good gear and higher end zones. This isn't always a bad thing but because people are going to level pretty fast and the population of the server is going to be pretty high this will leave many players&amp;nbsp;with no access to that content, which for&amp;nbsp;a lot of&amp;nbsp;people is the whole reason they&amp;nbsp;want to play this server to experience older content. I think there is a way to make the game more fun for more people.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Let the Combine server go as normal until Planes of Power is unlocked (since I see a lot of posts that seem to think this is where the game became unfun for them). At that point have a quest or something that allows people to do a turn in that transports them to PoK but moves them to a different server. The second server can then continue the progression, while progression then stays static on the Combine. This may satisfy many of the Classic server people as well as the slower casual players who where restricted from much of the content because they could not compete the big guilds. The big guilds still get to have there competition and they will now have access to old zones if they want to help gear up their guilds without blocking the&amp;nbsp;casual players from experiencing that content. It will also keep the casual crowd from quitting because they can't compete, because they can look forward to the top guilds moving on at some point. The transfer will not only be available to the&amp;nbsp;people&amp;nbsp;who completed the high end luclin content but anybody who wants after it is unlocked. If the Combine&amp;nbsp;struggles because lack of players, who cares, move them all to the second server and close it ( I doubt it will have that problem at least until most people finish the luclin content).&amp;nbsp;Then start a new progression server, a pvp progression server, or whatever you want to do with the hardware. I guess if it needs to be closed that should quit the people calling for a classic server because it would be obvious it is not viable. I don't see any downside except for you need another server, but not until PoP is unlocked which will probably be a while from now and that will give SoE plenty of time to gauge how successful the server. One possible problem I can think of is that when the slower players finally finish Luclin and decide it is time for them to move to the new server, depending on how far behind everyone else is they may have a hard time getting a guild doing PoP progression and may end up in the same position they are in on current servers. But, probably there will be guilds working on PoP progression for quite a long time because there will be a steady stream of people coming from the Combine.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What do you guys think?&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
