&lt;P&gt;Maybe I was not clear based on the replies. What I meant was have 2 servers have one not progress past Luclin, but when people want to move on to PoP they actually transfer to the second server. The second server will have all expansions up to PoP unlocked from the time they transfer and when players move to that server they will pick up progression from there trying to unlock the next expansion and continue up to the current expansion. Only the first server will remain static and not progress past Luclin,&amp;nbsp;the 2nd will continue to progress. If the first server needs to be closed eventually they will just merge into the second server, but that doesn't seem like it would really matter that much since everyone on both servers began the progression at the same time. Some will just be further ahead than others, but that would be the case whether there were 2 servers or just one. &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If you don't like the idea or don't think it will work that's fine, It just didn't seem like you understood what I meant from your replies.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
